By LULAMILE FENI and MALIBONGWE DAYIMANI Chaos erupted at the Mthatha High Court when awaiting-trial-prisoner Luthando Mndayi, of Payne Farms village, near Mthatha, attempted to escape after first stabbing a policeman on Monday. He was shot dead while trying to attack another officer, said Mthatha cluster police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Mzukisi Fatyela yesterday. In Mdantsane, two awaiting-trial prisoners Thabani Mkhokheli, 30, and Lulekani Somtsora, 25, escaped from the Regional Court holding cells yesterday after their lawyer left them unattended after finishing consulting with them. National prosecuting authority spokesman Tshepo Ndwalaza said their attorney had to rush to another case and the prisoners, facing charges of armed robbery, were left with no guards. For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions. It was high drama at the Mthatha High Court premises  yesterday when a group of eight trial-awaiting prisoners staged a daring escape by overpowering police officers and driving off in a police van. However five were captured less than an hour after the escape following a high-speed car chase involving… December 8, 2015 In "News" Drama ensued at the Mthatha High Court this afternoon after an awaiting trial prisoner was shot dead after he stabbed and seriously wounded a policeman. The inmate is believed to have attempted to escape when he stabbed the warrant officer Mthatha Cluster police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Mzukisi Fatyela said the incident… October 9, 2017 In "Featured" Eight awaiting trial prisoners who were in the Mthatha High Court stole a police van and escaped from the court this afternoon. They were about to be transported back to the Mthatha prison when the incident happened. It is not clear  at this point how they got hold of the police… December 7, 2015 In "News"